714248f-a.title: Manhattan: 68th Street (West) - Amsterdam Avenue
714248f-a.text:
West 68th Street, and Amsterdam Avenue, 'orth west
corner showin P.S. 94.
Board of Education, N.Y.C.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATINE.  1920.

715949f-a.title: Manhattan: Amsterdam Avenue - 68th Street (West)
715949f-a.text:
Amsterdam Ave., east side, north from West 68th Street (right) to
Sherman Square (left, caused by convergence and intersection of Amsterdam
Ave. and Broadway at West 72nd Street), showing prominently the ''Nevada'',
an apartment hotel, occupying the southern apex of the Square and
occupying that triangular block between 69th and 70th Streets. The
southern side of this structure, forming the north side of 69th Street
appears illuminated across a gas station on the opposite side.
December 19, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

714247f-a.title: Manhattan: 68th Street (West) - Amsterdam Avenue
714247f-a.text:
155 West 68th Street, north side, between Amsterdam Avenue and

P. L. Sperr.
